text: Kadsura Kaempf. Ex Juss., 1810 is a genus of plants. It has 16 species of bejucos woody plants. It belongs to the family Schisandraceae. Its type species is K. japonica (L., 1753) Dunal, 1817. == Uses == Some species have uses in gardening. Category:Flowering plants Category:Plants of Asia
title: Kadsura
